# do-while Loop

`do-while` is like `while`, but the condition is checked **after** each iteration. So the code always runs at least once.

```php
do {
    // code
} while (condition);
```

Note the semicolon after the condition.

```php
<?php
$i = 1;
do {
    echo "i is $i\n";
    $i++;
} while ($i <= 3);
// Output: i is 1, i is 2, i is 3

// Even if condition false initially, runs once:
$j = 10;
do {
    echo "This runs once.";
} while ($j < 5);
// Output: This runs once.
?>
```

